Company description: ELECTRO DEPOT is a retail company that specializes in the sale of electronic products and home appliances at reduced prices. The company's mission is to make electronic equipment accessible to everyone by offering a wide range of products, from household appliances to smartphone accessories, while ensuring optimal quality. Committed to sustainability, ELECTRO DEPOT aims to reduce its carbon footprint by 50% per product sold by 2030, reflecting its dedication to minimizing environmental impact. The clientele primarily consists of individuals seeking great deals, as well as professionals looking to equip their workspaces with reliable electronic solutions.  ELECTRO DEPOT collaborates with various partners to provide products from well-known brands, maintaining competitive pricing without compromising on quality. The company caters to a diverse target market that includes tech enthusiasts and everyday consumers who value both affordability and reliability in their electronic purchases. Through its physical stores and online platform, ELECTRO DEPOT enhances the shopping experience by offering convenient delivery options and a user-friendly purchasing process. By focusing on customer satisfaction and accessibility, ELECTRO DEPOT continues to establish itself as a go-to destination for quality electronic products at budget-friendly prices.

Company description: IVS France is a leading player in the vending industry, specializing in the provision of hot and cold beverages and snacks through advanced automatic and semi-automatic vending machines. As a key member of the IVS Group, which operates across several European countries, IVS France is dedicated to delivering high-quality products and services while emphasizing sustainability and social responsibility. The company's mission is to create long-term value for its stakeholders, including employees, customers, and local communities, by focusing on quality, risk management, and environmental benefits.  IVS France serves a diverse clientele, including businesses, institutions, and public services, and collaborates with various partners to enhance its service offerings. The company is committed to promoting a culture of sustainability, focusing on the circular economy to minimize waste and enhance the quality of life for future generations. With a workforce of approximately 79 employees, IVS France prioritizes employee well-being and responsible marketing practices, aiming to be a benchmark in the vending market. The company operates around 280,000 vending machines across several European countries, including Italy, Spain, and Switzerland, and boasts a workforce of approximately 4,000 employees. IVS France's innovative approach includes the use of satellite communication and telemetry systems to ensure maximum efficiency and product integrity. The company also enhances the customer experience with user-friendly payment systems and a dedicated mobile application, Coffee cApp, allowing users to purchase products directly from their smartphones. IVS France is committed to creating enjoyable break areas that foster employee well-being and productivity while engaging in eco-friendly practices and supporting local suppliers. Through its initiatives, IVS France strives to contribute positively to the communities it serves and uphold high standards of quality and responsibility. With a strong emphasis on consumer satisfaction, technological innovation, and environmental sustainability, IVS France aims to transform the coffee break experience into a moment of connection and inspiration.

Company description: MedVir for ‚ÄúVirtual Medicine‚Äù is an outstanding medical decision support expert solution. This unique artificial intelligence system based on Fuzzy Logic, is an intelligent medical system modeled on the reasoning of an emergency physician. Its role is to assess the patient‚Äôs condition by asking questions. Powered by over 30 years of research (field medicine and learned society), based on evidence-based medicine, this artificial intelligence system meets 3 needs: assess the seriousness of a condition, propose diagnostic hypotheses & guidance ‚Ä¢ MedVir Pre-Diag covers all symptoms, all speciality, all common & urgent diseases + 31 Rare diseases. In conclusion, MedVir provides: ‚Ä¢ A limited number of diagnostic hypotheses ‚Ä¢ The assessment of the seriousness of the situation (CCMU scale), ‚Ä¢ A Medical guidance (what to do, OTC drugs, explanations, etc. ) ‚Ä¢ An encyclopedic explanation for all the considered diagnoses. ‚Ä¢ An automatic anamnesis report, storable, printable, shareable, integrable. MedVir is both for patients, and for healthcare professionals (nurse, doctor, pharmacist, paramedic, etc.). MedVir is in SAS mode, easily interoperable, available on any medium (computer, smartphone, tablets, etc.). All the data are anonymous, unambiguously stored and searchable, for real time epidemiology. MedVir is in: French, English, Italian, Spanish, Brazilian. MedVir is a Class I Medical Device since 2017, designed & rigorously controlled by physicians with demonstrated reliability.
